\begin_layout Title
Experimentally suppress residual geometric dephasing use a single trapped
 ion
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
Geometric phase also known as Berry phase, is regarded as a pential strategy
 in fault tolerance quantum information processing(QIP) due to it's geometric
 nature.
 Traditional dynamic decoupling sequence can eliminate dynamic dephasing
 while residual geometric dephasing is still import for high-precision quantum
 manipulation bathed in environmental noise .
 Following the schemes in Ref.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "qin2017suppressing"

\end_inset

, we experimentally demonstrate using a single trapped 
\begin_inset Formula $^{171}Yb^{+}$
\end_inset

 ion that these modified dynamic decouping sequences suppress residual geometric
 dephasing effectively.
 Besides, we also investigate the impact of intensity and correlation time
 of the low-frequence noise on coherence.
 And we confirm the domain of validity of these methods.
 
\end_layout

