\begin_layout Standard
Dephasing arises in quantum systum when the interaction between system and
 environment causes randomizaiton of its quantum phase in a process
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "arai2018geometric"

\end_inset

.
 Part of this dephasing is dynamic dephasing while part of this is of geometric
 origin.
 Although dynamic dephasing can be supressed throuth spin echo methods
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "jones2000geometric"

\end_inset

 and geometric dephasing is much less than dynamic one
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "de2003berry"

\end_inset

.
 Residual geometric dephasing is still important for precise control and
 high fidelity gate manipulation.
 Recently, more and more work have investigated the geometric contribution
 to dephasing
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "whitney2005geometric,berger2013exploring,berger2015measurement"

\end_inset

.
 New schemes was proposed to suppress the residual geometric dephasing in
 Ref.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "qin2017suppressing"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this Letter, we investigate the geometric dephasing under classical Ornstein-
Uhlenbeck(OU)
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "gillespie1996exact"

\end_inset

 fluctuating field using a quantum two-level system(TLS) in a ultracold
 ion.
 Utilizing modified dynamical decoupling schemes such as SE and CPMG
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "bylander2011noise"

\end_inset

, we suppress the residual geometric dephasing effectively.
 Furthermore, by altering the intensity and correlation time of noise, we
 demonstrate the scope of application of our schemes in real experiment.
\end_layout

