\begin_layout Standard
In our experiment, Berry phase and coherence of the qubit have been measured
 as a function of angle spanned by the magnetic field 
\begin_inset Formula $\textbf{B}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{z}$
\end_inset

 axis.
 Using a spin echo pulse sequence, in which dynamic phase will be offset
 by opposite loop direction of neighboring adiabatic evalution, we can measure
 pure Berry's phase.
 The experiment takes the following process: after 1ms doppler cooling,
 the state of the ion is initialized to 
\begin_inset Formula $|0\rangle$
\end_inset

 by 20
\begin_inset Formula $\mu s$
\end_inset

 standard optical pumping.
 Then a series of coherent manipulations will be bring to the ion using
 a bunch microwave 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{mw}$
\end_inset

.
 In order to observe different Berry Phase with different angle 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

,we vary 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{mw}$
\end_inset

 around qubit transtion frequency 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{0}=12.64GHz$
\end_inset

, which will causes different 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta=arctan\frac{\Omega}{\Delta}$
\end_inset

.
 The 
\begin_inset Formula $2\pi$
\end_inset

 time for Rabi oscillation is adjusted to 
\begin_inset Formula $95\mu s$
\end_inset

, that is, the Rabi frequency 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega=10.5kHz$
\end_inset

.
 The complete sequence start by preparing the 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{z}$
\end_inset

 superposition state with a 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi/2$
\end_inset

 resonant microwave.
 Then the magnetic field traces around 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{z}$
\end_inset

 axis adiabaticly by varying 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi$
\end_inset

, the phase of mircowave slowly, causing one of the eigenstate 
\begin_inset Formula $|+\rangle$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $H_{1}$
\end_inset

 acquire a phase 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma_{+}=\gamma_{d}+\gamma_{g}$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma_{d}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma_{g}$
\end_inset

 are dynamic and geometric phase respectively.
 we make 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{\varphi}/B=0.1$
\end_inset

, which guarantee the adiabatic parameter 
\begin_inset Formula $A=0.05sin\theta\ll1$
\end_inset

.
 A resonant 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi$
\end_inset

 pulse then swap the eigenstate of Hamiltonian in 
\begin_inset Formula $(1)$
\end_inset

, after which the magnetic tracing along opposite direction causing the
 same eigenstate of 
\begin_inset Formula $H_{1}$
\end_inset

 acquire 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma_{+}=-\gamma_{d}+\gamma_{g}$
\end_inset

.
 Finally the pure geometric phase difference between engenstates is 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta=\gamma_{+}-\gamma_{-}=-4\pi cos\theta$
\end_inset

.
