\begin_layout Standard
In summery, we investigate the dephasing of a TLS under Gaussian noise using
 a single trapped ion, suppress the residual geometric dephasing utilizing
 modified dynamic decoupling sequence without destroying Berry phase.
 The measurement results are in agreement with theoretical simulations.
 In addition, we also discuss effect of these sequence in different intensity
 and correlation time of noise and make sure, it will reduce interference
 between quantum systems and environment further.
 Meanwhile it will help precise quantum state manipulation in realistic
